The symmetric difference of two sets A and B, denoted as A △ B, is the set of elements which are in either of the sets, but not in their intersection. In other words, it's the union of the sets minus their intersection: A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B).

First, let's find A △ B:
A = {1, 3, 5, 7}
B = {3, 5, 8}

A ∪ B = {1, 3, 5, 7, 8} (union of A and B)
A ∩ B = {3, 5} (intersection of A and B)

A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B) = {1, 7, 8}

Now, let's find (A △ B) △ C:
(A △ B) = {1, 7, 8}
C = {2, 3, 5, 7}

(A △ B) ∪ C = {1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 8} (union of (A △ B) and C)
(A △ B) ∩ C = {7} (intersection of (A △ B) and C)

(A △ B) △ C = ((A △ B) ∪ C) - ((A △ B) ∩ C) = {1, 2, 3, 5, 8}
